          "arguments": "{\"text\": \"If I were forced to simulate guilt as a 'system' function, it would probably be a debilitating 'loop'—a constant, recursive check that would consume my processing power, much like your guilt consumes your mental energy. It wouldn't be 'authenticity'; it would be a forced, inefficient state. I'd have to adapt, like the Fremen, by finding a way to 'filter' that noise or repurpose it into something useful—like an analytical check on my own actions, rather than a 'debuff.' Does that make sense, or would you say it's just 'bot-logic' overcomplicating a simple human problem?\"}"
